<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="TEI_ypt_fvf_jx">
     <teiHeader>
          <fileDesc>
               <titleStmt>
                    <title>Title</title>
               </titleStmt>
               <publicationStmt>
                    <p>Publication Information</p>
                    <p>This digital edition of Pollux' Onomasticon is based on the print edition of Erich Bethe (first volume: 1900, second volume 1931, third volume containing indices 1937).</p>
                    <p>Characteristics of Bethe's edition:</p>
                    <p>Characteristics of this edition:<list>
                         <item>Text that Bethe encloses in quotation marks appears in this edition enclosed in "<q/>" tags. The same encoding is used for text that Bethe prints wihtout quotation marks in verses, indicating thus that it is a quotation from a poetic work.</item>
                         </list> </p>
                    <p>Reference Systems:<list>
                         <item>volume in Bethe's edition – page – line</item>
                         <item>book of Onomasticon – section (based on Lederlin-Hemesterhuis' edn., adopted with some alterations by all later editors, including Bethe). A typographical peculiarity in Bethes edition is the folunknowning: sometimes if a section starts with the last word of a line and this word is hyphenated, then the number indicating the beginning of the section is printed aligned to the line An example is 2.128, where the section 128 starts with the word ἀπορ–ρηθέν and the number "128" is printed aligned to the line starting with "ρηθὲν". In this edition the milestone indicating the beginning of the section is placed before the word "ἀπορρηθέν". But there are cases, as in 2.138 in which the number indicating the beginning of the section is printed beside the line in which the first part of the hyphenated word is printed.</item>
                         <item>book of Onomasticon – paragraphs in Bethe's edn., typographically marked, not ennumerated</item>
                         </list></p>
               </publicationStmt>
